manufacturerProductDescription.media_text: Best for Multi-Display When people buy GPUs, it's usually for running video games, but if you just want a display output, the AMD Radeon R5 230 might just be what you're looking for.With just 160 CUDA cores, 625 MHz engine clock, and 1GB video memory, this card will have difficulty running modern video games and even most of the old ones. However, it's the perfect choice for non-gamers with a CPU that doesn't have integrated graphics or those who want to set up a secondary display. This low profile, low power consumption card will improve multimedia performance, extend the desktop, and accelerate apps.For flexibilty of use, it comes with a Low Profile bracket so it can be used in a Small Form Factor chassis or HTPC configuration. This GPU comes with a dual-link DVI port, an HDMI port, and a VGA port — allowing you to set up three more displays without spending a lot of money. The maximum power draw of 18 watts makes it suitable for systems with a power supply capacity as low as 300 watts. Something to consider: To emphasize it further, this GPU is not meant for gaming, so don't expect it to run video games well. It's best for those who need extra space to manage non-demanding software like word documents and web browsers.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 24, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Good for a old pc to media center
reviews.reviewText: This runs as a home media center in a older amd machine, running debian 12. No driver issues or system stability issues, It handles dual monitors just fine.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on March 6, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Great product for streaming video from pc to TV
reviews.reviewText: I have an old computer that needed an hdmi, for my big screen TV. I did not want to spent a lot. So when I found this one, the price was right but I was a little skeptical that it would work on a 10 year old computer with Window 7. After I inserted the QTHREE AMD Radeon R5 230 Graphics Card, I booted up my pc and plugged in my monitor and I deleted all existing drivers. Then I downloaded the drivers for this pacific graphics card per instructions that came in the box. But my pc would lock up a short time after each reboot. So I uninstalled the drivers I downloaded and just did a Windows 7 update, which updated the drivers. Now everything works great. I can view both the monitor and TV and the same time, or have an extended view version of both.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on October 15, 2022
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Works on linux
reviews.reviewText: I got this to replace a Nvidia graphics card on a linux computer. It worked immediately without any fuss (unlike the Nvidia). It sometimes glitches bit (window droppings for example), but so far it's an improvement.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on August 15, 2022
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Worked on my Linux Mint 20.3
reviews.reviewText: The graphics chip that was built into my motherboard was older and not fully compatible with Linux Mint 20.3. Periodically it would cause screen tearing. This card fixed the problem and was also low power enough as I only had a 200w power supply in the old computer.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on April 7, 2023
reviews.reviewText: very disappointed with this video card it only has 3 settings for the screen and they all make the pictures/ikon starched out or wide screen I pulled out and went back to the old video card

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on September 30, 2022
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Works just fine
reviews.reviewText: Installed it to get more memory on a video card and can tell the difference going from 500MB to 2GB. Love it. Had to download an AMD driver that matched the model of this card and now all is working perfect. Very satisfied. Thanks.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on July 4, 2022
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars I got what I expected.
reviews.reviewText: I didn't need much in a graphics card. I put this in an old machine for a Batocera build. It did exactly what I wanted. It's quiet and Batocera is much smoother compared to the integrated graphics. I had this installed and the machine up and running in 5 minutes.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 22, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 3.0 out of 5 stars NOT for gaming, good for word processing, desktop apps, bad on streaming
reviews.reviewText: I got this to accelerate basic video functions, but this did not do it. Not at all for high speed gaming, good for taking the load off for networking purposes, streaming and video playback are hindered but VERY good at accelerating desktop functions. Not better than most modern on board video processors. Use this for point of sale machines, desktop publishing (not video), word processors, server video.
